title: Philippines Exports
description: Exports in Philippines increased to 7157467.37 USD Thousand in September from 6410888.05 USD Thousand in August of 2022. Exports in Philippines averaged 1860679.17 USD Thousand from 1957 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 7170937.30 USD Thousand in March of 2022 and a record low of 23000 USD Thousand in October of 1957. Exports in Philippines account for nearly a third of GDP. Major exports are: electronic products (42 percent), other manufactures (10 percent) and woodcrafts and furniture (6 percent). Philippines is also the worldâ€™s largest producer of coconut, pineapple and abaca. Philippines's main export partners are: Japan (21 percent), the United States (15 percent), China (12 percent) and Hong Kong (8 percent).
